With the emergence of "No. 31" super-spreader, the transmission of the new coronavirus in South Korea also changed from "Foreign Import" to "community endogenous transmission" , and there were 4 deaths in succession.

This article first appeared at southern weekend and is not to be reprinted without permission

By Yao Mengmeng, southern weekend staff writer

Managing Editor | Dong Yu

Following the 22 cases reported on February 19,2020,229 new cases of coronavirus infection in South Korea were reported on February 22. February 23, South Korea added 123 new cases, a total of 556 confirmed cases of new coronavirus.

The outbreak in many parts of South Korea is urgent, and new coronavirus infections have spread throughout the country. Next, there will be more confirmed cases of suspected cases. As of press time, more than 22,000 people in South Korea had been tested for the new coronavirus, of which 6,039 had yet to be announced.

1
61-year-old "super spreader" appears, "hospital infection" impact on the medical system

1

###61-year-old "super spreader" appears, "hospital infection" impact on the medical system

"A 61-year-old woman living in Daegu city was tested for coronavirus and became the 31st confirmed case of the disease, " a spokesman for the Ministry of Central Epidemic Prevention said on February 20.

The 61-year-old woman was referred to by South Korean media as "No. 31" for short. She is believed to be the main cause of the spike in infections in Daegu city, where the "super-spreader" directly infected at least 37 people.

The route of infection remains a mystery, but the trajectory of her movements has been mapped out: She remained in Seoul and Taegu for a week after she developed a high fever.

She has participated in many new world church activities. By 4 p.m. on Feb. 22, at least 43 of the group's more than 8,000 followers in Daegu had been diagnosed, more than 400 had shown symptoms, and other members had been told to "self-quarantine. ".

"New World Church" has become a hotbed of virus transmission. Officials in the South Korean city of Daegu said 128 other confirmed cases in the city were linked to the new world church.

According to public records, the New World Church was founded in 1984 and has about 200,000 followers in South Korea and 120,000 in other countries and regions of the world. Founded by 89-year-old Lee Man-hee, he describes himself as the Bible's "shepherd of God's promises" and "Lord of Jesus's second coming. ".

"New World Church" engaged in controversial missionary activities and was identified by the Korean media as a "cult organization. Since then, 74 new world churches in Taegu and Gyeongbuk have been closed, while others have been converted to online missionary work.

The local government of Taegu has also announced the whereabouts of 31. At 3:30 p.m. on 17 February 2020, she developed severe fever and went to a local health centre for examination. She was then quarantined and admitted to Daegu city hospital.

After admission, "31" still led to a number of "hospital infection. Among them, a 40-year-old female staff member from Daegu Xinhan Hospital has been diagnosed, "31" has been to the emergency rooms of two other hospitals also closed the same day.

Emergency Room closures and "nosocomial infections" directly touched off public concern about the collapse of the country's health care and epidemic prevention system. As of February 21,2020, South Korea at least four groups of "hospital infection" phenomenon.

Among them, Gyeongsang North Road County Hospital has implemented a complete "closure" , the hospital has at least 16 confirmed, including 5 nursing staff, and about 600 medical staff and patients are undergoing further sampling.

2
The outbreak entered the "community transmission" , the barracks found more than cases

2

###The outbreak entered the "community transmission" , the barracks found more than cases

On February 22,2020,229 new cases of coronavirus infection were reported in South Korea on a single day. In the morning, 142 new cases were confirmed in South Korea. In the afternoon, another 87 cases were reported, including 69 in Taegu and North Gyeongsang Province, 5 in Gangwon Road, 4 in Gyeonggi Province, 3 in Seoul and 2 in Huangchuan County, ota, Busan, Ulsan and South Jeolla Province each had 1 case.

New Coronavirus infections have spread throughout Korea. On February 21,2020, there was no case of infection in Gangwon Province, in northeastern South Korea, and two confirmed cases emerged the next day. South Korea's central epidemic prevention department requires vigilance around the "local outbreak of growth. ".

Thus, South Korea has also become after the Chinese Hubei and docked in Port of Yokohama, Japan, "Diamond Princess" outside the two "cluster infection" area. February 18,2020, the South Korean government decided to "Diamond Princess" to send Air Force 3 aircraft, bring back six South Koreans and a Japanese spouse and seven others.

The first death in South Korea was a young man. At 9:05 a.m. on February 18,2020, Seoul's Koongoku district received a report that a man in his 30s was unconscious and had not inhaled. After being transferred to the hospital, the man died at 10:30 that morning.

"there were signs of bleeding in the lungs, " said the South Korean daily Chosun Ilbo, adding that the man had travelled with his family to Hainan, China, for three days last month.

On February 20,2020, there was a second death in South Korea. The deceased was a 63-year-old man with underlying illness who had been hospitalized for many years for schizophrenia in a hospital in Qingdaokong, North Gyeongsang. After the patient's death, South Korean health authorities tested him for the virus and the results were positive.

The third fatality was a 41 year old man who was found dead at his home in Gyeongju, North Gyeongsang Province, where autopsy tested positive for the new coronavirus. The fourth fatality was a 57-year-old man who worked at Qingdaonan Hospital in North Gyeongsang Province. Tests for the virus are still being carried out.

The new crown outbreak also threatens South Korean military camps. A 22-year-old marine became South Korea's first confirmed case of the disease when he was visiting his family in Taegu.

As mentioned above, Daegu has a "local outbreak of infection. ". There is also a large number of South Korean troops stationed there and a United States military base, with military and civilian personnel and their families totaling more than 10,000 people.

The US military has restricted access to military bases and quarantined and quarantined US personnel who come into contact with the church.

The South Korean military has also begun quarantine and isolation. According to Yonhap, at least three South Korean soldiers have been diagnosed with the infection, and the number is likely to rise because as many as 1,000 South Korean soldiers have visited Taegu and Gyeongbuk since February 10.

To prevent the spread of the epidemic in military camps, all military bases in the Republic of Korea declared an emergency closure on 22 February and raised the danger level. All officers and soldiers were cancelled their leave and going out.

3
The government set up a "special administrative region" of the epidemic, people are still large-scale rallies

3

###The government set up a "special administrative region" of the epidemic, people are still large-scale rallies

On February 21,2020, South Korean Prime Minister Chung Sye-kyun declared the cities of Daegu and North Gyeongsang Province as "special administrative areas for infectious diseases" .

Currently, about 70 percent of new coronavirus cases are in the "special administrative region. ". Taegu, with a population of 2.5 m, is South Korea's fourth-largest city, with confirmed cases in schools and hospitals and a large number of suspected cases occupying 87.5 per cent of the city's hospital beds.

"This is an unprecedented crisis, " said Taegu's mayor, who ordered people not to leave their homes without masks and temporarily closed businesses.

But "Special Administrative Region" does not seem to be the same as "closed city. ". On February 21st Yonhap News Agency reported that the streets of Taegu were still full of people. On the 23rd, the streets of Taegu were deserted.

On February 21,2020, after the South Korean government declared Taegu and other places as "special administrative regions" , I found that many people on the Seoul subway had been wearing masks.

South Korea's Seoul Metropolitan Government also announced the same day: Suspension of all activities in the city assembly, violators of a fine of 3 million won.

But many South Koreans still insist on large-scale gatherings despite government bans. On February 22,2020, tens of thousands of people marched from the Gwanghwa Gate and Seoul Railway Station near the assembly, held protests as scheduled.

Live footage on South Korean television showed many demonstrators standing next to one another, many without masks, and even handing out bread, cakes and other food items to each other.

"please stop the rally and think about your own safety and that of others, " said Seoul Mayor Park Won-soon, who arrived to dissuade the marchers from returning home.

"It's impossible to catch [ the new coronavirus ] outdoors, " a rally organizer said in a speech near Gwanghwamun

"The window of opportunity is narrowing, " the central government of South Korea and the Central Government's epidemic prevention department agreed that the spread of new coronavirus infection has reached "extremely serious" level, but the South Korean government appears to have been hesitant to respond to the outbreak.

February 22,2020, South Korea Central Emergency Response Department Deputy Minister Buddha's warrior attendant Lee said at a press conference, the government decided not to raise the new crown epidemic alert level, still maintain the "alert" level; The highest "serious" level is taken only when there is "community transmission across the country" .

Some South Korean scholars believe that since 2019, the South Korean economy is facing the "worst situation" in 50 years, the South Korean government is not willing to "over-vaccination" and hurt economic growth.
